<title>FRANCE: Jospin reaffirms commitment to single currency.</title>
<headline>Jospin reaffirms commitment to single currency.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-07-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin reaffirmed on Thursday that France's Socialist-led government was committed to launching a single European currency.</p>
<p>&quot;We want to launch the single currency because it is necessary,&quot; he said in a television interview.</p>
<p>It was the only way to fight against currency speculation and growing power of the U.S. dollar, he said.</p>
</text>
